USERMOD - Command used to change login user information to lock a user or disable account, this is one of important command in system administration
Adding user to secondary group
  #usermod –aG ‘group name’ ‘username’   -- a stands for append
#usermod –aG wheel taylor
Adding comment to user
#usermod –c ‘user info’ ‘username’
#usermod –c ‘Contract base’ taylor
Changing user home directory 
    by default /home is default home directory
#usermod –d ‘new home directory path’ ‘username’
#usermod –d /testhome taylor  
When taylor login next time his present working directory will be /testhome
Renaming username
#usermod –l ‘new user name’ ‘old user name’
#usermod –l kalyan taylor
Changing user expiry date
#usermod –e ‘expiry date in yyyy-mm-dd’ ‘username’
#usermod –e 2026-03-30 kalyan
To change it to never expire
#usermod –e “” ‘username’
#usermod –e “” kalyan
#chage –l kalyan  -- expiry date should be changed to March 30 2026
Locking and Unlocking user  
User will login with SSH keyless authentication, only locked direct logins all pam based authentications will be successful.
#usermod –L ‘username’
Unlocking User
#usermod –L ‘username’
